6 unit potatoes
2 unit courgette
1 packet chicken thigh
2.5 tbs plain flour
2 sachet Sweet Mustard Spice Mix
olive oil
½ tsp salt
1 packet Smokey Aioli
2 head broccoli
2 tsp honey
1 packet Dijon mustard

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut the potato (unpeeled) into 2cm chunks. Place the potato on an oven tray lined with baking paper. Drizzle generously with olive oil, season with a good pinch of salt and pepper and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 25-30 minutes. TIP:  Cut the potato to the correct size so it cooks in the allocated time.

While the potato is roasting, thinly slice the courgette into batons. Cut the broccoli into small florets and roughly chop the stalk. Slice the chicken thigh in half.

In a medium bowl, combine the salt, plain flour, sweet mustard spice blend and a pinch of pepper. Add the chicken and toss to coat. In a large frying pan, heat a good drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the chicken and cook, turning occasionally, until golden and cooked through, 10-14 minutes. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel. TIP:  The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside!  TIP:  If your pan is getting crowded, cook in batches for the best results.

When the potato has 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a medium frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add the broccoli and a splash of water and cook until just tender, 4-5 minutes. Add the courgette and cook until tender, 3-4 minutes.

Remove the frying pan from the heat and add the Dijon mustard and honey. Toss to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper. TIP:  Hold back on the mustard if the kids aren't fans!

Divide the Southern-style seared chicken, honey-mustard veggies and the roast potato between plates. Serve with the smokey aioli.